HEADWORD: Papist
<hw>Pa"pist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>papiste</ets>. See <er>Pape</er>, <er>Pope</er>.]</ety> <def>A
Roman Catholic; one who adheres to the Church of Rome and the authority
of the pope; -- an offensive designation applied to Roman Catholics by
their opponents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

